Create a Spring @Service class named ReimbursementNotificationService under package com.medgo.reimburse.service.

This service is responsible for sending reimbursement submission email notifications to both the admin/reimbursement system and the end user.

Functional requirements:

Use OpenFeign (NotificationServiceClient) to call an external email notification service.

Read admin email and email image path from application properties.

Support HTML email content.

Prevent duplicate emails for the same control code within a configurable time window (5 minutes).

Ensure thread-safe idempotency using ConcurrentHashMap, synchronization, and a lock object.

Email sending flow:

Expose a public method sendControlCodeEmail(ReimbursementSubmissionResponse response, String deviceId, String applicationId, String userEmail).

Validate control code before proceeding.

Ensure only one email is sent per control code within the deduplication window.

Send one email to the admin email address (including bank details).

Send one email to the user email address (excluding bank details), if valid and different from admin email.

Handle concurrent calls safely and avoid duplicate sends.

Email content handling:

Build rich HTML email templates.

Attempt to load an image from src/main/resources using ClassPathResource.

Convert the image to Base64 and embed it inline in the email body.

If the image fails to load, fall back to a pure HTML email template.

Display control code prominently in the email.

Include bank account details only for admin emails.

Escape all dynamic values to avoid HTML injection.

Add a disclaimer and privacy link at the bottom of the email.

Error handling & logging:

Handle Feign errors, decode exceptions, and unexpected runtime exceptions gracefully.

Log success, failures, retries, and skipped duplicate sends clearly.

If email sending fails, remove the control code from the deduplication map to allow retry.

Implementation details:

Use Lombok annotations (@Slf4j, @RequiredArgsConstructor).

Use @Value for configuration properties.

Use helper methods for:

Validating email addresses

Building HTML email bodies (with and without images)

Building bank details sections

Loading images as Base64

Determining image MIME type